CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 30, 1951, pg. 5 reads: "Murray Made Life NAACP Member At Banquet - At a testimonial banquet in William Penn Hotel last Thursday, Philip Murray, CIO and Steelworkers president, was honored by top-flight persons in local civic life, both white and Negro, for his efforts at interracial harmony. Here Mrs. Daisy Lampkin, Courier vice president, presents Mr. Murray with a life membership in the NAACP while County Commissioner John Kane (seated), looks on. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Daisy Lampkin standing next to guest of honor Philip Murray behind William Penn Hotel podium for testimonial banquet, with John Kane seated in background
